### SEG-T-7: Founder Paste-Ready Launch Instructions

Write `BISHOP_DROPZONE/00_FOUNDER_REVIEW/MESH_TEST_RUN_INSTRUCTIONS.md` with the following steps:

**Step 1.** Download MnemosyneC-Setup-0.1.35.exe on M2 (192.168.86.45) and M3 (192.168.86.64). Install. Accept SmartScreen prompt.

**Step 2.** On M2: open MnemosyneC, go to WelcomeView "Just use it" doorway, choose Activate FULL. This triggers the Gemma 4 12B pull (~5 GB). Repeat on M3.

**Step 3.** Wait for Gemma pull to complete on both M2 and M3. Estimated time: 10 to 30 minutes per machine depending on LAN speed. The Settings -> AI Tier screen shows pull progress.

**Step 4.** On M1: open MnemosyneC, click "Prove it with a test" -> "Google benchmark set, standard" (MMLU-Pro Standard tier). Confirm M2 and M3 appear as active peers in the mesh view before starting.

**Step 5.** M1 orchestrates: shards the dataset, sends shard manifests to M2 and M3, all three nodes run locally. M1 shows aggregation progress. Do not close MnemosyneC on any machine during the run.

**Step 6.** When the run completes: view the Big Numbers card in the WelcomeView accordion, open the results JSON and markdown summary from the dropzone, review the SVG charts.

**Estimated wall-clock time:** Standard tier (~12K questions): 2 to 4 hours total across 3 nodes in parallel (each node processes ~4K questions). Diamond tier (~2K questions): 30 to 60 minutes. Resource budget: CPU and RAM only, no GPU required, no API cost.

Yoke-return: the completed `MESH_TEST_RUN_INSTRUCTIONS.md` file ready for Founder to read without modification.

